Hi Alan

If you have a lot of code unindented you can use Vim (I know, that's
probably not what you meant by &quot;program&quot;, but maybe it helps). Here's how
you can indent a whole file with a few comands:

1) Open the file inside Vim
2) While in editing mode, press G, then =, and then Esc.

The whole file should now be properly indented.

I think you need the vim-ruby plugin installed, otherwise Vim might not know
how to indent the erb syntax.

Cheers,
Caio

