Hi Alan

I've just tested the command again and it didn't work (don't know why it did
the first time). There's another way to do it:

1) Open the file inside Vim
2) While in editing mode (and on the first line), press Shift ^ V (to get in
visual mode), then Shift ^G (to select all the lines), and then =

